        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "4.利用经纬网定位",
          "block_bbox": [
            140,
            327,
            656,
            401
          ],
          "block_id": 1,
          "block_order": 1
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "1)经纬网的含义：在地球仪或地图上经线和纬线相互交织所构成的网络。",
          "block_bbox": [
            220,
            438,
            2006,
            508
          ],
          "block_id": 2,
          "block_order": 2
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(2)经纬网的作用：确定地球表面某一点的位置。",
          "block_bbox": [
            225,
            545,
            1372,
            613
          ],
          "block_id": 3,
          "block_order": 3
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "地球的运动",
          "block_bbox": [
            151,
            754,
            468,
            816
          ],
          "block_id": 4,
          "block_order": 4
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "1.地球的自转",
          "block_bbox": [
            166,
            861,
            516,
            923
          ],
          "block_id": 5,
          "block_order": 5
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(1)含义：地球绕着地轴不停地旋转。",
          "block_bbox": [
            234,
            963,
            1141,
            1041
          ],
          "block_id": 6,
          "block_order": 6
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(2)方向：自西向东.",
          "block_bbox": [
            239,
            1068,
            673,
            1151
          ],
          "block_id": 7,
          "block_order": 7
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(3)周期：一天(约为24小时).",
          "block_bbox": [
            239,
            1177,
            907,
            1237
          ],
          "block_id": 8,
          "block_order": 8
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(4)产生的现象：昼夜更替、地方时差",
          "block_bbox": [
            237,
            1279,
            1106,
            1358
          ],
          "block_id": 9,
          "block_order": 9
        },
        {
          "block_label": "paragraph_title",
          "block_content": "2.地球的公转",
          "block_bbox": [
            139,
            1491,
            537,
            1553
          ],
          "block_id": 10,
          "block_order": 10
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(1)含义：地球围绕太阳不停地旋转。",
          "block_bbox": [
            241,
            1596,
            1170,
            1678
          ],
          "block_id": 11,
          "block_order": 11
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(2)方向：自西向东。",
          "block_bbox": [
            243,
            1702,
            697,
            1780
          ],
          "block_id": 12,
          "block_order": 12
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(3)周期：一年(约为365天).",
          "block_bbox": [
            242,
            1806,
            881,
            1870
          ],
          "block_id": 13,
          "block_order": 13
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(4)特点：地球公转的轨道平面与地轴的央角是66.5°",
          "block_bbox": [
            240,
            1909,
            1546,
            1993
          ],
          "block_id": 14,
          "block_order": 14
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(5)产生的现象：",
          "block_bbox": [
            241,
            2018,
            627,
            2085
          ],
          "block_id": 15,
          "block_order": 15
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "①太阳直射点在南北回归线之间来回移动；",
          "block_bbox": [
            311,
            2128,
            1324,
            2202
          ],
          "block_id": 16,
          "block_order": 16
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "②同一地点，太阳高度角的变化；",
          "block_bbox": [
            313,
            2232,
            1056,
            2310
          ],
          "block_id": 17,
          "block_order": 17
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "③同一地点，昼夜长短的变氏：",
          "block_bbox": [
            310,
            2336,
            1016,
            2418
          ],
          "block_id": 18,
          "block_order": 18
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "④同一地点，不同季节太阳光热不同，即春夏秋冬四季的形成。",
          "block_bbox": [
            307,
            2444,
            1733,
            2524
          ],
          "block_id": 19,
          "block_order": 19
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "（6)$=\\sqrt{2}-\\frac{1}{2}$ ：春分日(3月21日前后）、夏至日(6月22日前后)、秋分日(9月23日前后)、冬至日((2月22日前后)\n",
          "block_bbox": [
            121,
            2548,
            2049,
            2730
          ],
          "block_id": 20,
          "block_order": 20
        },
        {
          "block_label": "text",
          "block_content": "(7)四季的划分(以北半球为例，南半球正相反)：",
          "block_bbox": [
            223,
            2754,
            1380,
            2846
          ],
          "block_id": 21,
          "block_order": 21
        },
        {
          "block_label": "number",
